1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:02,276
Welcome to Reparenting Your Inner Child.

2
00:00:02,276 --> 00:00:06,548
This practice helps you offer care to a
younger part from your present-day Self.

3
00:00:06,548 --> 00:00:08,916
Begin by settling into a comfortable
position.

4
00:00:08,916 --> 00:00:10,681
Take a slow breath in.

5
00:00:19,681 --> 00:00:19,681
<break time="3s" />

6
00:00:19,681 --> 00:00:20,935
And let it out.

7
00:00:20,935 --> 00:00:23,396
Imagine a younger part of you who may
need attention.

8
00:00:35,396 --> 00:00:35,396
<break time="3s" /><break time="3s" />

9
00:00:35,396 --> 00:00:37,068
You do not need to force an image.

10
00:00:37,068 --> 00:00:40,976
You may sense an age, a feeling, a
memory, or simply the presence of a

11
00:00:40,976 --> 00:00:41,712
younger part.

12
00:00:41,712 --> 00:00:45,102
Ask gently: Would it be okay if I came
closer?

13
00:00:57,102 --> 00:00:57,102
<break time="3s" /><break time="3s" />

14
00:00:57,102 --> 00:00:59,563
If the part says no, respect that.

15
00:00:59,563 --> 00:01:02,860
If the part says yes, imagine approaching
with warmth and patience.

16
00:01:14,860 --> 00:01:14,860
<break time="3s" /><break time="3s" />

17
00:01:14,860 --> 00:01:16,625
Ask: What did you need back then?

18
00:01:28,625 --> 00:01:28,625
<break time="3s" /><break time="3s" />

19
00:01:28,625 --> 00:01:29,368
Listen.

20
00:01:47,368 --> 00:01:47,368
<break time="3s" /><break time="3s"
/><break time="3s" />

21
00:01:47,368 --> 00:01:51,120
Maybe the part needed protection,
comfort, belief, encouragement,

22
00:01:51,120 --> 00:01:54,520
stability, permission to feel, or
permission to be a child.

23
00:01:54,520 --> 00:01:58,049
Now ask: What do you need from me now?

24
00:02:10,049 --> 00:02:10,049
<break time="3s" /><break time="3s" />

25
00:02:10,049 --> 00:02:11,442
Listen again.

26
00:02:11,442 --> 00:02:13,346
Offer only what feels honest.

27
00:02:13,346 --> 00:02:18,932
You might say: I am here now. You matter
to me. I want to learn how to care for

28
00:02:18,932 --> 00:02:23,516
you. You did not deserve to be alone with
that. We can go slowly.

29
00:02:32,516 --> 00:02:32,516
<break time="3s" />

30
00:02:32,516 --> 00:02:35,813
Now imagine giving this child part
something supportive.

31
00:02:47,813 --> 00:02:47,813
<break time="3s" /><break time="3s" />

32
00:02:47,813 --> 00:02:53,486
A blanket. A safe room. A hand to hold. A
comforting phrase. A protective boundary.

33
00:02:53,486 --> 00:02:54,593
A place to play.

34
00:03:03,593 --> 00:03:03,593
<break time="3s" />

35
00:03:03,593 --> 00:03:04,615
Let the part choose.

36
00:03:04,615 --> 00:03:07,169
Now ask: How do you feel toward me right
now?

37
00:03:19,169 --> 00:03:19,169
<break time="3s" /><break time="3s" />

38
00:03:19,169 --> 00:03:20,702
Do not force trust.

39
00:03:20,702 --> 00:03:22,885
If the part is unsure, that is okay.

40
00:03:22,885 --> 00:03:25,811
Trust is built through repeated care.

41
00:03:25,811 --> 00:03:29,248
Ask: What is one way I can show up for
you this week?

42
00:03:41,248 --> 00:03:41,248
<break time="3s" /><break time="3s" />

43
00:03:41,248 --> 00:03:42,130
Listen.

44
00:04:00,130 --> 00:04:00,130
<break time="3s" /><break time="3s"
/><break time="3s" />

45
00:04:00,130 --> 00:04:02,731
Choose one small reparenting action.

46
00:04:02,731 --> 00:04:07,347
Maybe speaking kindly to yourself, taking
rest seriously, setting a boundary,

47
00:04:07,347 --> 00:04:11,658
making space for play, writing to the
younger part, or returning to this

48
00:04:11,658 --> 00:04:12,205
practice.

49
00:04:12,205 --> 00:04:13,970
Now thank the younger part.

50
00:04:13,970 --> 00:04:15,735
Let them know you will keep learning.

51
00:04:24,735 --> 00:04:24,735
<break time="3s" />

52
00:04:24,735 --> 00:04:26,128
Take a slow breath in.

53
00:04:35,128 --> 00:04:35,128
<break time="3s" />

54
00:04:35,128 --> 00:04:36,196
And let it out.

55
00:04:36,196 --> 00:04:37,589
Return gently to the room.

